  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">WASH Emergency Response - East Ghouta and Afrin displacement</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project addresses the immediate WASH needs of internally displaced people from East Ghouta and Afrin. Over 50,000 people from East Ghouta are hosted in collective centres, with the numbers continuing to increase. Most of the shelters do not have the capacity or infrastructure to accommodate the large number of people arriving. The shelters are extremely overcrowded and severely lacking water, sanitation and hygiene facilities. In Afrin, over 100,000 men, women and children are estimated to be have been displaced. The majority have fled to Tal Refaat, with the remainder going to surrounding areas.

This project has been designed against the latest OCHA collected information and analysis of the humanitarian and protection situation. SHF funds will be used to procure life-saving WASH NFIs, the installation of water tanks, provision of water trucking, construction and rehabilitation of existing latrines in the collective shelters, the rehabilitation of existing sewage networks within collective shelters and the installation of prefabricated latrines.

WASH supplies will be distributed to all the shelters to meet the immediate needs of the most vulnerable population. Some sites already have over 16,000 IDPs with available toilet facilities for no more than 1,000 people. IDPs have no possibility to leave the camp, most of these sites have no showers and most of the IDPs have not had a shower or changed of clothing in over 1 month. In some of these sites, in particular on arrival, IDPs have no access to toilets. Use of open defection within the site is common. If the situation is not addressed immediately, there is a real risk of outbreak of communicable diseases incl. cholera.</narrative>
  </description>
